The paper presents a new network architecture that integrates optimization problems as individual layers in larger end-to-end trainable deep networks. This makes it likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper presents a new network architecture that can be trained end-to-end, making it likely to belong to this sub-category. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper highlights the application of the proposed approach in several problems, including image classification and object detection, making it likely to belong to this sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents a new approach that can learn hard constraints better than other neural architectures, making it likely to belong to this sub-category. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new neural network architecture that integrates optimization problems as individual layers, making it likely to belong to this sub-category. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a highly efficient solver for the proposed layers that exploits fast GPU-based batch solves within a primal-dual interior point method, making it likely to belong to this sub-category.
